REQUIREMENTS
=============

CRISP requires the SAMtools package (http://samtools.sourceforge.net/) to read BAM files.


HOW TO COMPILE THE CODE
========================

1. Download the SAMtools package from sourceforge: http://sourceforge.net/projects/samtools/files/samtools/0.1.18/
On the command line, Samtools can be downloaded using the command "wget http://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/samtools/samtools/0.1.18/samtools-0.1.18.tar.bz2"

Note that CRISP may not compile with the newer version of samtools (v1.1) 

2. Untar the file samtools-0.1.XX.tar.bz2 to create the directory "samtools-0.1.XX" and run make inside the 
"samtools-0.1.XX" directory. Note that on Ubuntu, you may have to install libncurses5-dev and zlib1g-dev in order to 
compile samtools. 

3. Download the CRISP source code and untar to create the CRISP directory

4. Modify the Makefile in the CRISP directory to point to the location of the 'samtools' directory

   change the "SAMTOOLS=" variable to point to the path for the samtools directory 

5. run 'make all' to create the CRISP executable. The CRISP executable will be placed in the 'bin' directory 

